Soylennial obsession with high school never fails to fascinate me. Especially the "social" aspects, "cliques", "nerds vs. jocks", TV show tropes from various sitcoms that haven't been reflected in reality for years and exist purely as psychological anxieties in 29-35 year olds.

When you watch older Millennial leftists they always talk like "lol this guy is such a weird nerd, dude", they even used to fantasize about stuffing people into lockers, just an absolutely bizarre collection of feverish cultural residue, platitudes, false memories, memes, tropes.

It reminds me of how dementia patients sometimes start to believe they are in high school while in their nursing home. Or like the gas station owner's amnesiac wife in Twin Peaks. You have to be old to romanticize what is essentially a government mandated time tax on young people
